race.comment: OUTTA LINE (10) began poorly then rallied late and just missed in a brave effort over the mile at Warwick Farm last start, her first defeat at start three. Won on debut on a soft track so she is likely to handle this ground. Won't mind the extra trip and can bounce back to winning ways. MIRRA IMPACT (3) had no luck at all last time out over 1600m at Warwick Farm so his effort to be beaten on 2.4 lengths had merit. Won consecutive races at the provincials on slow/heavy tracks earlier this campaign. Poses a big threat. WILLIE OPPA (11) scored a barnstorming win over the Randwick mile two back then again found the line strongly in a similar race last start. Drops back to midweek company - one of the better chances. EXISTENTIAL BOB (5) has been in the money at his last three. Rock hard fit and both his wins have come on rain-affected tracks. Market watch on French import MAUPASSANT (2) first-up from an eight-month spell for the Archibald stable.
